<h3><u>&nbsp;Refund & Cancellation Policy</u></h3>
   
    
    <ul type="disc">
        <li>
            <p style="text-align: justify; padding: 10px">
                Ticket purchased through the web should be cancelled only through the web/BMET call
                center by passengers/web agents, the amount will be refunded only in the account
                by which ticket booked. The system will generate a unique ID, by deducting the cancellation
                charges as applicable. This unique ID can be produced at our office for refund or
                can submit request for online refund against provided refund unique ID.<br />
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p style="text-align: justify;padding: 10px; border:1 px">
                Strictly no cancellation of ticket same day of journey prior to 6 hour of 
                departure. Ticket can be cancelled 24 hours before the date of journey, with 20% cancellation charges through web, for less there 
                6 hour cancellation please call BMET call center to get assistance in cancellation. Please note that the cancellation fee and cancellation period may differ from one bus operator to another.<br /><br />
             Cancellation Charges:<br />
        Prior to 24 hrs of departure time - 20% deduction<br />
        Between 24 hrs to 12 hrs before departure time – 30% deduction<br />
        Between 12 hrs to 6 hrs before departure time – 50% deduction<br />
        Prior to 6 hrs of departure time -No Cancellation
                </p>
        </li>
       
    </ul>
